Routine Jonglei State CBMC data analysis

Summary

This is a routinely prepared summary of CBMC data from Lankien. This report contains data up to 2020 W39 and provides information on consultation numbers, malaria, awd, respiratory tract infections and highlights some data quality issues.

  • Consultations
    • In 2020 W39 the four week rolling average of consultations was 130, 68, 74, 146 and 158 in Nyambor, Nyatim, Pathai, Riang and Yuai respectively. Clear differences in consultation patterns across the CBMC sites with Nyambor showing regular numbers over time period. The other sites seem to show greater or lesser effects of seasons on consultation numbers.

  • Malaria
    • In 2020 W39 the four week rolling average of malaria positive consultations was 16, 22, 5, 17 and 36 in Nyambor, Nyatim, Pathai, Riang and Yuai respectively. Much larger and clearer malaria peaks in Pathai, Riang and Yuai compared to Nyambor and Nyatim.

  • Data quality for malaria diagnoses. In 2020, we see that there were 6, 1, 2, 6 and 5 months with discrepancies in the number of malaria diagnoses and number of RDT positive cases in Nyambor, Nyatim, Pathai, Riang and Yuai respectively.
